Program: Outlook
Title: Outlook: Life, the Second Time Around
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cstzbd
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 23 Oct 2017
Five years after he had been declared dead in a canoeing accident, John Darwin walked into a police station. Where had he been and what had he been doing? Californian James Vlahos had a great relationship with his father, so when he was told his dad was dying he had to do something to preserve his memory. He got hold of specialist software, and started typing up some of the things his dad had said to him and made what he calls a 'Dadbot' Image: Computer generated fragmented blue head Credit: Pobytov/GETTY IMAGES Show less